                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Affliction Focus -- forget it
<br />
Enhancement Haste IV:  Good for Arcane Rune until you get enough Quick Buff levels.  Marginally useful in raid buffing after that.
<br />
Extended Enhancement IV:  You can switch this in and out.    Speed of Valon is 42 minutes.  With 15% --> 48 minutes.  Enough for you to finish a LDoN if you are running up against the time limit.  The 8th prayer shawl works here (20%, so 50 minutes).
<br />
Extended Range IV:  Essential in charming or pacifying.
<br />
Extended Torment IV: Marginal improvement.  Probably not worth it.
<br />
Improved Damage IV:  Depends on how much you nuke.
<br />
Innoruuk's Sarcasm:  Lets you Tash a little bit earlier.  Not A-list unless you are your guild's primary tasher.  Plus Tashicide is much less common now than during Velious/Luclin era.
<br />
Mana Preservation IV:  Yes.  Definitely. No Question.  It's like FT when you are working.
<br />
Spell Haste IV:  Charm goes a little faster.  Slow goes a little faster.  If you use those spells, then this is a good thing.
<br />

<br />
Some of these things can be switched in and out.  The pottery items (Ceramic whatevers) are relatively cheap, but pretty bad stats otherwise.  Ornate has many of these focus effects.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37024" target="_blank" class="postlink">Serius</a>, Enchanter to King Tearis Thex on the Luclin Server
<br />
<span style="color: darkred">Dead enchanters take no faction hits</span>
