                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For general use, I'd get these:
<br />

<br />
Mana Pres IV
<br />
Innoruuk's Sarcasm
<br />
Extended Torment IV
<br />
Extended Enhancement IV (or Zephyr of Brell)
<br />

<br />
The only thing I think spell haste is good for is charming because mez casts faster than 3.0, which is the minimum limit for spell haste. And of course, quick buff is better for arcane rune.
<br />

<br />
For raiding, you often need to stay out of range of some very nasty AEs, especially in PoP. For that, some kind of extended range focus is good. There are a lot of PoP items with Druzil's Distance, which is even better than regular ER4. This is also good for places like sol ro's tower where the agro range is equal to the normal range of Pacification, and let's you single pull when it would otherwise be impossible.
<br />

<br />
For charming, anything that lets you recharm before the mob reaches you is a big help. Extended range, and spell haste are what you need here.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
