                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Mana Preservation:</span> This is a must have. Also this is the only focus that actually improves exponentially, not linearly (5% from 10% to 15% increase is worth less than 5% from 20% to 25% increase)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Spell haste</span> A definite plus both when soloing and raiding (slow, cripple, nuke, etc). As an aside you should get Quick Buff maxed (or covered with enhancement haste)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Extended range</span> Very good for solo and AE avoidance as others have said. Also has nice niche uses (pacifying in solro or cats during MM encounter etc)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Extended Duration</span> Very nice to have, but then again AAs can make up for a lack of item.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Improved Damage</span> If you want to up your DPS. Bare in mind it only dishes out half given % on average. (so 20% added damage is only worth about 10% actual more damage)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Extended Torment</span> nice, but I tend to work with an innate mez-refresh clock. If it doesnt add a fixed duration I wont rely on it, so until GoD AAs get out and I got proof they stack with this focus I wont bother much with it.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Burning Affliction</span> worthless, as I cant see any point in using our DoTs
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Innoruuk's Sarcasm</span> I'd like to know if there is an aggro reduction cap . If it is the case I dont really see the need for this. Get SCS (20%) and cast Beguiling Visage (50%) when it really matters.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
